-- China shares dip after property data, Great Wall Motor slides
-- 
-- Thu Apr 17, 2014 11:59PM EDT
-- None



BEIJING, April 18 (Reuters) - China shares fell slightly on Friday, weighed down by property stocks after home price data for March showed a further cooling in the real estate sector.

By midday, the Shanghai Composite Index <.SSEC> was down 0.1 percent at 2,096.30 points. The CSI300 <.CSI300> index of the largest Shanghai and Shenzhen A-share listings was flat. House prices in China's 70 major cities grew 7.7 percent in March compared with a year earlier, slowing from last month's 8.7 percent rise, according to Reuters calculations based on official data. [ID:nENNE4G0RY] China Fortune Land Co Ltd <600340.SS> fell 2.6 percent, Shanghai Jinqiao Export Processing Zone Development Co Ltd <600639.SS> shed 2.2 percent and Ningbo Fuda Co Ltd <600724.SS> dropped 2.4 percent. Great Wall Motor Co Ltd <601633.SS> slid 5.2 percent, becoming the morning's biggest loser in the CSI300 index, after the country's top maker of sport utility vehicles and pick-up trucks posted a sharp slowdown in first-quarter earnings growth.[ID:nWNBS00FBS] ZTE Corp <000063.SZ>, China's second-biggest maker of telecommunications equipment, gained 1.6 percent after the company reported a tripling of net profit in the first quarter.[ID:nL3N0N310B]